--- Switchblade ---

He hears the message and is immediately suspicious. He hadn't 
heard, seen, or picked up any signals entering the atmosphere, 
and he can't remember anybots named Wingspan. It does occur to 
him that he hadn't been created for long before he'd been launched 
off planet, and he hadn't gotten to meet all of the Decepticons. He 
continues trying to fix the central console in the base. He thinks to 
himself, <I'll run a traceroute program on this frequence, and locate 
the bot, when I get the console fixed.> He sends an encrypted 
commlink to all Decepticons, who he knows are a part of the 
faction, "Decepticons, do NOT respond to that unknown message 
from a bot calling himself/herself 'Wingspan', I'd like confirm his 
validity, with Lord Megatron's permission of course." He frowns, 
Megatron was still suspicious from the Motormaster incident, this 
might help smooth things over a bit. He continues working on the 
console, he is almost finished.


On 12 Jun 2001, at 19:43, LurkerAbyss wrote:

> ::Hakibuscon::
> 
>     Hakibuscon approached the Decepticon base with caution,
>     transforming to robot mode.  He activated his stealth mode, which
>     made him invisible to the defenses.  He sent a message through to
>     all Decepticons in the Dark Avian.
> 
>     "Fellow Decepticons!  Do you hear me?  It's me, Wingspan!  I'm
>     alive!  I've got a new body, but I'm still a Decepticon, always
>     and forever!" Hakibuscon said, faking his identity.  He learned
>     that a bounty hunter should never reveal his true identity.
